This article is a transcript of a joint press conference between President Obama and President Chinchilla of Costa Rica. The two leaders discussed various topics including institutional strengthening, international policy, security, energy, and education. They emphasized the importance of working together to address issues such as drug trafficking and organized crime. President Obama also expressed his support for comprehensive immigration reform and recognized the contributions of Costa Ricans in the United States. President Chinchilla discussed the need for open and respectful debates in Costa Rica on issues such as same-sex marriage and the control of firearms.